<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1893-06-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1893-06-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="557" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d557">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Gresham</persName> to Sir
                                    <persName type="to">Julian Pauncefote</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1893-06-19"><hi rend="italic">June 19,
                                1893</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Important communication sent you to-night concerning Samoa. After you
                            have read it I suggest it necessary that I confer with you and German
                            minister here as soon as possible.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">W. Q. Gresham.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>